## What This Repository Is

This repository defines Constraint-Native Infrastructure Governance (CNIG), a conceptual framework for reasoning about admissible system states in distributed and AI-integrated systems.

The framework investigates whether governance in complex systems may require:

> structural admissibility filtering over reachable state space prior to execution.

CNIG is not a product, enforcement platform, orchestration engine, or deployment specification.

It is a systems reasoning framework.

