# Core Recognition Pattern

CNIG investigates systems where:

* local correctness exists
* runtime observability appears healthy
* yet global system behavior becomes unstable or unsafe

The framework models this as:

> admissibility failure under composition

---

# What CNIG Does NOT Claim

CNIG does not claim:

* universal formal verification
* AGI alignment capability
* complete governance enforcement
* full system-state enumerability
* runtime implementation feasibility

The framework is exploratory and theoretical.

